Description

A black and white photographic print of Jazzy Joyce.

Joyce is pictured in an interior room, next to a large window with broken panes of glass and an open door behind her. Her hair is pulled back, she is wearing hoop earrings, and she is smiling wide with her mouth open. She is wearing a white sweatshirt with the sleeves rolled up. There is a drawing on the shirt which includes a record and a car. The front tire of the car reads [JAZZY / JOYCE] while the rear tire reads [JOYCE / JETTA]. There is text on the proper left side of the shirt which reads ["JAZZY JOYCE" / SPEEDIN' FASTER / THAN A EIGHTY-SIX / 'JETTA'!]. She is wearing a black cross-body purse on her left shoulder, bracelets, and several necklaces. Her arms are out to the sides. There is grafitti on the wall behind her.

There are no marks or inscriptions, front or back.
